SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 455
By Bailey
A RESOLUTION to recognize Lanny Selby on the occasion of his
retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that the members of this General Assembly should honor
those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm in securing the
safety of their community; and
WHEREAS, Lanny Selby is one such estimable individual, who, following thirty-three
years of devoted service to the Sparta Fire Department, will take his much-deserved retirement
from his post, drawing an end to his career as a firefighter; and
WHEREAS, Lanny Selby has performed his duties with professionalism and integrity,
helping his fellow citizens in any way that he could and proving himself time and again to be a
tremendous asset to the City of Sparta; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Selby exemplifies the spirit and allegiance to family and community that
are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, throughout his career, Lanny Selby has demonstrated the utmost
professionalism, ability, and integrity, winning the respect and admiration of his fellow
firefighters and the residents of Sparta; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Lanny Selby on his
exemplary career with the Sparta Fire Department and extend to him our best wishes for much
continued success and happiness during his retirement.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
